OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778817909
OL,3,CStudent dies in Reading meningitis
OL,4,Coutbreak as contacts offered
OL,5,Cantibiotics
OL,7,FHenley College, in Henley-on-Thames,
OL,8,Fis a sixth-form college with more than
OL,9,F2,000 full-time students which teaches
OL,10,Fmore than 60 A-level subjects and
OL,11,Fvocational diplomas, according to its
OL,12,Fwebsite.
OL,14,FOn Thursday, Dr Paddy Woodman,
OL,15,Fdirector of student services at the
OL,16,FUniversity of Reading, said: "While
OL,17,Fthere are no reported cases among
OL,18,FUniversity of Reading students, I know
OL,19,Fthat our students, staff and family
OL,20,Fmembers may be concerned.
OL,26,@xD@^OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778817909
OL,3,CStudent dies in Reading meningitis
OL,4,Coutbreak as contacts offered
OL,5,Cantibiotics
OL,7,F"We will be contacting students to
OL,8,Fremind them of existing information
OL,9,Fabout looking out for signs of
OL,10,Fmeningitis, and the importance of
OL,11,Facting immediately on any worrying
OL,12,Fsymptoms, as well as checking their
OL,13,Fvaccination status."
OL,15,FTwo students died in a meningitis
OL,16,Foutbreak in the Kent area in March `
OL,17,F18-year-old Juliette Kenny, who was
OL,18,Fdescribed by her family as "fit,
OL,19,Fhealthy and strong" before her death,
OL,20,Fand a University of Kent student.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@TO]zD@\OU{D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778817909
OL,3,CStudent dies in Reading meningitis
OL,4,Coutbreak as contacts offered
OL,5,Cantibiotics
OL,7,FDr Rachel Mearkle, consultant in
OL,8,Fhealth protection, said: "We
OL,9,Funderstand that many people will be
OL,10,Faffected by this sad news and would
OL,11,Flike to offer our condolences to the
OL,12,Ffriends and family of this student.
OL,14,F"Students and staff will naturally be
OL,15,Ffeeling worried about the likelihood
OL,16,Fof further cases, however
OL,17,Fmeningococcal meningitis requires very
OL,18,Fclose contact to spread and large
OL,19,Foutbreaks as we saw in Kent recently
OL,20,Fare thankfully rare.
OL,26,@pD@ZOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778817909
OL,3,CStudent dies in Reading meningitis
OL,4,Coutbreak as contacts offered
OL,5,Cantibiotics
OL,7,F"We are working closely with partners
OL,8,Fand have provided public health advice
OL,9,Fand precautionary antibiotic treatment
OL,10,Fto close contacts of the cases.
OL,12,F"Meningococcal disease does not spread
OL,13,Feasily and the risk to the wider
OL,14,Fpublic remains low."
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUvD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
