PN,30210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778817909
OL,3,CStudent dies in Reading meningitis
OL,4,Coutbreak as contacts offered
OL,5,Cantibiotics
OL,7,FMeningitis Now's chief executive Dr
OL,8,FTom Nutt said: "Everyone at Meningitis
OL,9,FNow is deeply saddened and concerned
OL,10,Fto hear reports of a suspected
OL,11,Foutbreak of meningitis affecting young
OL,12,Fpeople in Reading and the surrounding
OL,13,Farea, including the tragic death of a
OL,14,Fyoung person.
OL,16,F"We would urge people to remain
OL,17,Fvigilant and aware of the signs and
OL,18,Fsymptoms of the disease. Meningitis
OL,19,Fcan become life-threatening very
OL,20,Fquickly and early diagnosis and
OL,21,Ftreatment are absolutely vital."
OL,26,@pD@POUxD@AOU}D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1778817909
OL,3,CStudent dies in Reading meningitis
OL,4,Coutbreak as contacts offered
OL,5,Cantibiotics
OL,7,FAccording to Dr Nutt, symptoms can
OL,8,Fappear in "any order" and may include
OL,9,Fa high temperature, severe headache,
OL,10,Fvomiting, stiff neck, sensitivity to
OL,11,Flight, confusion, drowsiness, cold
OL,12,Fhands and feet, severe muscle pain,
OL,13,Fand a rash that does not fade under
OL,14,Fpressure.
OL,16,F"Teenagers and young adults are among
OL,17,Fthe groups most at risk from
OL,18,Fmeningococcal disease, and the recent
OL,19,Foutbreak in Kent has shown how quickly
OL,20,Fcases can emerge," he added.
OL,26,@pD@KOUpD@UO]xD@AOU|D@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
